This paper deals with optimizing video delivery over wireless networks, which involves aspects of networking, multimedia, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of buffering and rate adaptation, which are common topics in multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes an optimization problem and uses mathematical modeling, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of prediction and knowledge of available resources, which are topics in Information Theory (cs.IT).
